In its pursuit to provide tailor-made solutions for small and medium enterprises (SMEs), MTN Nigeria has supported the recently concluded SME Clinic facilitated by Techpoint Africa held, in Lagos. The SME Clinic was developed to assist Nigerian Start-ups scale their businesses leveraging the power of technology. Senior Manager, SME Segment Management, Enterprise Business Unit (EBU), MTN Nigeria, Damilola Runsewe, presented various solutions created by the company to assist businesses in Nigeria. He explained that products like the Hynetflex and CallAssists helps with the growth of small businesses.
Runsewe, reiterated MTN’s continued support for businesses in the country, saying: “It’s 2020 and the business world is more competitive than ever. With our understanding of the policies, new developments, the rapid digitisation of businesses in Nigeria and the rest of the world, we have decided to take necessary steps in pulling others along. “We are always stronger together and all the businesses you see here form vital parts of the building blocks of our economy.
“We hope that as we have provided knowledge on various skills and shared how solutions can be derived using various EBU products, these business owners would imbibe it and create a stronger system.” MTN’s Enterprise Business Unit was created to foster long term trusted-partner relationships with the company’s customers, by bringing technology to work seamlessly. The unit constantly anticipates customer needs in solution-development